1
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:11,390
If you're the center...

2
00:00:11,390 --> 00:00:12,970
Aren't you taking Jeng’s spot?

3
00:00:12,970 --> 00:00:14,090
No.

4
00:00:14,090 --> 00:00:15,350
I can be in any position.

5
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:17,430
As long as it benefits our group.

6
00:00:17,710 --> 00:00:19,440
I want you to apply for a job there.

7
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:20,670
Tomorrow morning.

8
00:00:20,670 --> 00:00:21,460
Okay?

9
00:00:21,460 --> 00:00:22,130
Oh.

10
00:00:22,490 --> 00:00:23,660
Bitter melon, be my love.

11
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:26,660
There are songs about sharks and mangosteens.

12
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:28,710
Now it's time for bitter melons.

13
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,450
So I came to the right place.

14
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:33,720
Ultimate Wolf agency.

15
00:00:33,720 --> 00:00:36,250
I hope I finally pass the audition this time.

16
00:00:41,020 --> 00:00:42,870
Sorry, I wasn’t looking.

17
00:00:42,870 --> 00:00:43,870
I’m really sorry.

18
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,340
It’s okay.

19
00:00:45,340 --> 00:00:46,560
I wasn’t paying attention.

20
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:48,140
Well,

21
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:51,080
are you auditioning for Ultimate Wolf too?

22
00:00:51,980 --> 00:00:52,660
Mhm.

23
00:00:53,130 --> 00:00:54,410
Nice to meet you.

24
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:56,460
I hope we'll meet again at the agency.

25
00:00:57,330 --> 00:00:58,520
Then I’ll go audition first.

26
00:01:09,740 --> 00:01:10,470
Hello.

27
00:01:10,990 --> 00:01:12,980
Is this Ultimate Wolf agency?

28
00:01:13,850 --> 00:01:14,480
Yes.

29
00:01:15,890 --> 00:01:16,960
I'm here to audition.

30
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:18,900
What's your name?

31
00:01:19,250 --> 00:01:19,980
I'm Jeng.

32
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:34,260
Hey.

33
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:35,510
Why is it that...

34
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:37,980
we’ve been brainstorming for a while,

35
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:39,570
but we still have no idea.

36
00:02:39,570 --> 00:02:42,780
Remember when we were at the noodle shop and you said,

37
00:02:42,780 --> 00:02:43,980
Bitter melon, be my love?

38
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,770
I thought we finally found our vibe.

39
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:49,770
Bitter melon, be my love.

40
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:52,240
Wanna be my love?

41
00:02:52,950 --> 00:02:54,110
May I have a bitter melon?

42
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:01,220
Hey, let’s keep going.

43
00:03:01,410 --> 00:03:02,140
Yeah.

44
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:03,800
I got it.

45
00:03:05,270 --> 00:03:05,890
Hey,

46
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,610
Do you eat bitter melon?

47
00:03:10,830 --> 00:03:12,470
Wanna be my love?

48
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,090
I can’t look away from you.

49
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:16,190
I’m going crazy.

50
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,950
That’s it. That’s the one!

51
00:03:22,130 --> 00:03:24,410
No way. That’s so good!

52
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,500
Ah!

53
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:33,140
We’re getting the hang of it.

54
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:35,800
Yeah, the ideas are pouring out now.

55
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,190
Let's keep going.

56
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:41,980
Now add some dance moves.

57
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:47,490
Just one look into your eyes

58
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:49,870
I almost lose my mind

59
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:54,620
I keep thinking about you every single night

60
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:57,070
You make me fall to my knees

61
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,480
And I don’t wanna wake up

62
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,430
It’s like you’re swallowing me whole

63
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:04,170
And I’m losing control

64
00:04:04,170 --> 00:04:06,650
You make me melt away

65
00:04:06,650 --> 00:04:08,940
My friends call me a fool

66
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:11,170
I wanna tell you that I’m fine

67
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:13,750
Beb’s mine to me

68
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:16,180
You make me be not free

69
00:04:16,180 --> 00:04:18,550
I wanna ask you to marry me

70
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:20,720
Meeting you, I’m not lonely

71
00:04:20,720 --> 00:04:22,570
Be happy to…

72
00:04:22,570 --> 00:04:25,870
Hey, do you eat bitter melon?

73
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:28,280
Wanna be my love?

74
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:30,400
I can’t look away from you

75
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,180
I’m going crazy because…

76
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:35,180
Hey, are you Google?

77
00:04:35,180 --> 00:04:38,470
You can find anything

78
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:40,540
But you’re my everything

79
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:42,230
I’m so fluttered because of (you)

80
00:04:47,990 --> 00:04:48,820
That’s amazing!

81
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,720
Excellent. Well done. Good job.

82
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,190
You all did a great job.

83
00:04:53,380 --> 00:04:54,170
Whoa.

84
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:58,400
I’ve never received this much praise

85
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,820
in my life before.

86
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:03,790
Tomorrow, get ready for a poster photoshoot.

87
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:07,120
Our group is going to be a hit.

88
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,830
Yeah!

89
00:05:09,830 --> 00:05:13,250
Hit, hit!

90
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,290
Keep fighting!

91
00:05:14,290 --> 00:05:16,970
You definitely won’t see this coming, Bai Liu.

92
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,550
Let’s go!

93
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,630
Hello. How are you doing?

94
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:34,020
You got the job?

95
00:05:34,470 --> 00:05:36,560
Great. How much is the salary?

96
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:38,200
Whoa.

97
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,990
So low!

98
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:41,940
Oh.

99
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:44,990
Wait, seriously?

100
00:05:47,670 --> 00:05:49,340
We have a situation!

101
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,820
What? Keep it down.

102
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,300
You’ll scare your roommate.

103
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:56,180
They’ve already formed a new group

104
00:05:56,909 --> 00:05:58,820
and have enough members now.

105
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,630
So how is it?

106
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,070
Does it look promising?

107
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,820
I’d say

108
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:06,710
it’s a total mess.

109
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:09,410
They’re all over the place.

110
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:11,380
But…

111
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:13,290
But what?

112
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:18,230
But there’s someone close to us in that group.

113
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:22,480
Really close.

114
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,950
Who is it?

115
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:27,900
It’s Si Mai, Tian’s younger brother.

116
00:06:28,210 --> 00:06:32,530
I think he’s helping them grab onto their last lifeline

117
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,920
before the company goes bankrupt.

118
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:39,380
I hope they succeed.

119
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:42,150
Go find out what they need for me.

120
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:45,150
If they lack or need anything,

121
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:47,010
tell me right away.

122
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,190
But…

123
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:51,720
don’t let them know I’m helping them. Got it?

124
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:52,820
Okay.

125
00:06:52,820 --> 00:06:56,260
I’ll keep it a secret.

126
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:59,050
For the sake of your love.

127
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,320
What love are you talking about?

128
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,180
Ridiculous.

129
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,780
I know it all.

130
00:07:05,780 --> 00:07:06,990
If you don’t believe me…

131
00:07:06,990 --> 00:07:08,020
Ask Roommate.

132
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:08,930
Ah!

133
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:11,650
See? Look at that.

134
00:07:11,650 --> 00:07:13,610
My Roommate is so smart.

135
00:07:13,610 --> 00:07:14,520
Right, baby?

136
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,770
Don’t bite him, baby.

137
00:07:18,310 --> 00:07:18,920
Let’s go.

138
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,310
You can go to the set now.

139
00:07:20,310 --> 00:07:20,950
Okay.

140
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,820
-Hello.
-Hello.

141
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:23,750
This is my first time.

142
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,850
The center, please stand in the middle.

143
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,430
Who’s the center?

144
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:29,760
What are you waiting for, Leader?

145
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,450
Come stand in the middle.

146
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,540
Come on, Leader!

147
00:07:35,530 --> 00:07:37,890
Okay, stand a little closer.

148
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:41,370
Okay, smile. One, two, three.

149
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:43,670
Okay, good.

150
00:07:46,820 --> 00:07:48,380
Okay, okay.

151
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,750
Give me a pose.

152
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,330
Nice. Next pose.

153
00:07:58,070 --> 00:07:59,690
You guys are having fun, huh?

154
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:00,620
Hello, boss.

155
00:08:01,730 --> 00:08:03,040
We’re having so much fun.

156
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,450
Thank you for trusting us.

157
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:11,770
And who is she?

158
00:08:12,230 --> 00:08:12,820
Ah.

159
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:15,160
I forgot to introduce you guys.

160
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,920
This is Medyer.

161
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:21,470
She’ll be your new manager from now on.

162
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,990
What about P’Somjai, P’Sommai, and P’Somruethai?

163
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:29,780
After careful consideration,

164
00:08:30,370 --> 00:08:32,990
P’Somjai, P’Sommai, and P’Somruethai

165
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:34,400
are biased toward that agency.

166
00:08:35,169 --> 00:08:38,510
We need someone professional,

167
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,280
who isn't a secret fan.

168
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:43,870
So I decided to restructure the team.

169
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:46,290
P’Medyer will take you to Siam Center.

170
00:08:46,820 --> 00:08:48,140
We’ll give you a makeover.

171
00:08:48,410 --> 00:08:51,230
She can sing

172
00:08:51,230 --> 00:08:52,450
and can write songs.

173
00:08:52,450 --> 00:08:53,600
Wow.

174
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:55,630
I’ll be in your care, P’Medyer.

175
00:08:56,120 --> 00:08:57,060
Rest assured.

176
00:08:57,570 --> 00:09:00,610
I’ll do my absolute best for you.

177
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,270
Great.

178
00:09:03,270 --> 00:09:04,490
I’ll be in your care.

179
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,000
Please take care of them.

180
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:08,540
Sure.

181
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,140
Jeng, you’re still here?

182
00:09:20,170 --> 00:09:20,990
I'm about to leave.

183
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:24,160
What about everyone else?

184
00:09:24,660 --> 00:09:25,470
Oh.

185
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:27,320
Something came up.

186
00:09:31,710 --> 00:09:32,680
Hey, bro.

187
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:34,090
You’re not going home?

188
00:09:34,410 --> 00:09:35,170
Not yet.

189
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,180
Go home safely. I’m leaving.

190
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:37,850
See you.

191
00:09:37,850 --> 00:09:39,040
My wife’s calling. See you.

192
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,380
Oh, you’re still not back, Mai?

193
00:09:45,100 --> 00:09:45,810
Not yet.

194
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,650
Why aren’t you?

195
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:52,350
Are you waiting for someone?

196
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:54,990
I’m not.

197
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:58,350
Bro.

198
00:09:58,350 --> 00:10:00,080
You’re so easy to read.

199
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:04,340
I’ve watched all of P’Option’s series.

200
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:06,820
The latest one is Duang With You.

201
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:11,280
It taught me that if you love someone, go for it.

202
00:10:11,980 --> 00:10:14,050
If you do nothing,

203
00:10:14,050 --> 00:10:16,110
you’ll never get what you want.

204
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:18,970
What nonsense is that?

205
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:22,820
Think about it.

206
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,360
Don’t let Khemjira be the only survivor.

207
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:28,680
You have to survive too.

208
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:29,450
Hey.

209
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:30,710
You’re overthinking.

210
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,280
Hey, Yu!

211
00:10:36,580 --> 00:10:39,050
You almost stepped on my new shoes.

212
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,530
Damn.

213
00:10:42,130 --> 00:10:43,020
Hello, P’Karn.

214
00:10:43,350 --> 00:10:45,410
What? Someone’s jumping off a building?

215
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,540
Oh my God!

216
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,120
I’m off work already.

217
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:51,570
I’ll hurry there.

218
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:52,930
Tell them to calm down.

219
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,440
Yu, someone’s about to jump.

220
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,400
We need to help.

221
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,050
Alright.

222
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:59,730
What about our barbecue buffet?

223
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:02,010
This is urgent. Let's talk later.

224
00:11:02,010 --> 00:11:03,980
Hey, wait.

225
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:07,110
Just singing won’t work. You need a rapper too.

226
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:09,500
Mai.

227
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,420
Jeng might be in the bathroom.

228
00:11:11,420 --> 00:11:12,290
I’ll leave him to you.

229
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:14,240
Oh.

230
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:16,820
Turn right.

231
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,620
Yu is such a volunteer at heart.

232
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:25,340
I'll give you a ride.

233
00:11:25,850 --> 00:11:26,720
Get in.

234
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:29,720
It’s okay. I’ll take the MRT home.

235
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,450
Will you make it in time?

236
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:34,730
It’s almost midnight.

237
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:36,630
My house is nearby.

238
00:11:37,270 --> 00:11:39,680
I can get there in no time.

239
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:42,090
Alright, I’m heading out. Bye.

240
00:11:42,820 --> 00:11:44,820
Uh…

241
00:11:44,980 --> 00:11:45,800
Wait, Jeng.

242
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:47,410
Uh…

243
00:11:47,860 --> 00:11:49,520
So... my car ran out of gas.

244
00:11:50,340 --> 00:11:51,450
Can I go with you?

245
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,020
Mhm.

246
00:12:14,780 --> 00:12:15,820
So cute.

247
00:12:15,820 --> 00:12:16,720
Huh?

248
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:19,820
Your bag.

249
00:12:20,650 --> 00:12:21,660
It's kinda cute.

250
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:23,160
Oh.

251
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:26,270
I can change pictures too.

252
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:27,220
-Really?
-Mhm.

253
00:12:27,650 --> 00:12:28,890
Just change it from my phone.

254
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:31,600
Tap the picture you want.

255
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,110
See? It changed.

256
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:34,510
Like this.

257
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:35,380
So cool.

258
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:38,150
You can even make it say hello

259
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:40,090
or add people’s faces.

260
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,390
See?

261
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,470
So it can turn into a heart too?

262
00:12:58,090 --> 00:12:58,770
Hey.

263
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:00,680
Do you listen to K-pop too?

264
00:13:01,410 --> 00:13:01,980
Yeah.

265
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:03,640
I listen to everything.

266
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,830
K-pop, T-pop, all of it.

267
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:06,760
-Really?
-Yeah.

268
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,390
Who’s your favorite group?

269
00:13:09,380 --> 00:13:11,610
CORTIS. I like Keonho.

270
00:13:11,610 --> 00:13:12,540
Watch this.

271
00:13:16,810 --> 00:13:19,550
That’s why you dress like him.

272
00:13:19,780 --> 00:13:20,960
What about you?

273
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,860
What music do you like?

274
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:24,900
Anything.

275
00:13:25,710 --> 00:13:27,490
I just hope I’ll have my own song one day.

276
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,010
You will.

277
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:32,260
We worked so hard, so we’re going to make it.

278
00:13:34,940 --> 00:13:36,640
(Next stop, Sanam Chai.)

279
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:39,180
Your mindset is good.

280
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,460
You always look so happy.

281
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:45,100
How?

282
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,210
Honestly,

283
00:13:48,890 --> 00:13:51,300
just chasing your dream is enough.

284
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,740
It gives your life meaning.

285
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:56,720
Which is way better than doing nothing.

286
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:01,840
That’s true.

287
00:14:02,180 --> 00:14:04,980
I’m getting off at the next station.

288
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:07,100
So,

289
00:14:07,810 --> 00:14:09,240
see you at the practice room.

290
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:11,200
Don’t be late,

291
00:14:11,730 --> 00:14:12,910
newbie.

292
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:15,680
Yes,

293
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,310
Senior.

294
00:14:19,530 --> 00:14:20,730
I’m heading off. Bye.

295
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:31,520
Jeng.

296
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:34,340
Good night.

297
00:14:37,220 --> 00:14:38,110
Bye.

298
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:39,590
Just one look into your eyes

299
00:14:39,590 --> 00:14:41,670
I almost lose my mind

300
00:14:41,670 --> 00:14:43,480
Be happy to…

301
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:46,770
Hey, do you eat bitter melon?

302
00:14:46,770 --> 00:14:49,190
Wanna be my love?

303
00:14:49,190 --> 00:14:51,300
I can’t look away from you

304
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,480
I’m going crazy because…

305
00:14:58,580 --> 00:14:59,410
Hello, Mai.

306
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:01,100
Where are you?

307
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,540
They said the studio’s closed,

308
00:15:03,130 --> 00:15:04,480
but your car is still there.

309
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,500
Do you want to pay the overnight parking fee?

310
00:15:06,790 --> 00:15:07,660
Oh, shoot.

311
00:15:08,110 --> 00:15:09,980
Thanks, bro.

312
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:23,880
Maybe…

313
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:27,290
Mai and I can be good friends.

314
00:15:37,230 --> 00:15:39,980
And one, two, three.

315
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:43,510
And ay.

316
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,420
Ta daa.

317
00:15:59,670 --> 00:16:00,500
Down.

318
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:02,340
And...

319
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:06,220
Okay, that’s it for today.

320
00:16:06,220 --> 00:16:08,380
Please practice the choreography,

321
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:09,600
and don’t mess up the moves.

322
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,500
See you all next week.

323
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,900
-Bye.
-See you next time.

324
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:18,380
I can smell success already.

325
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:20,140
Come here.

326
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,720
Let's stretch.

327
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:23,840
Alright.

328
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:27,680
If you guys dance this weak,

329
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:30,150
we won't be able to compete with others.

330
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:32,430
Let’s do it again.

331
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:34,370
Or am I wrong?

332
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,250
Hi, guys.

333
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:46,800
How’s practice going?

334
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,340
We’re trying our best.

335
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:51,440
We’re working hard, Boss.

336
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:52,740
Great.

337
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:56,190
I came to announce our debut and first single release date.

338
00:16:57,650 --> 00:17:01,500
And I’m taking you to a music show in Siam.

339
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:04,359
You’ll sit on the same chair

340
00:17:04,359 --> 00:17:06,230
that many Thai and Korean artists sat.

341
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,170
Now it’s your turn.

342
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:11,420
Really? We’re finally promoting our song?

343
00:17:11,690 --> 00:17:14,660
Are we gonna have fans waiting outside like other groups?

344
00:17:14,660 --> 00:17:15,819
Absolutely.

345
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,790
I bet there’ll be a lot of people.

346
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,990
But don’t worry.

347
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:24,339
I’ve already talked to Sean’s friend.

348
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:26,280
He’ll help us keep you safe.

349
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,390
Get ready for being famous!

350
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:33,360
We’re gonna be superstars!

351
00:17:35,820 --> 00:17:36,720
Come on.

352
00:17:41,380 --> 00:17:41,980
Hey.

353
00:17:45,670 --> 00:17:47,000
One, two, three.

354
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,980
Ahh Wolf!

355
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,230
Whoa.

356
00:17:57,220 --> 00:17:58,110
Whoa.

357
00:18:01,550 --> 00:18:02,680
Whoa.

358
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:05,130
Hm.

359
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,850
These clothes are so your vibe.

360
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:10,710
Why?

361
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:13,090
Because they’re cool like you.

362
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:15,100
Man.

363
00:18:15,330 --> 00:18:17,100
This shop totally fits us.

364
00:18:17,330 --> 00:18:18,600
How about this one?

365
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:20,850
Pretty cool.

366
00:18:21,430 --> 00:18:23,980
It’ll look great on you. Just get it.

367
00:18:25,670 --> 00:18:26,410
You know,

368
00:18:27,070 --> 00:18:29,200
having P’Medyer with us is actually nice.

369
00:18:29,980 --> 00:18:31,790
Even when she’s buried in work,

370
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,080
she still gets everything done.

371
00:18:34,790 --> 00:18:36,940
Look at Fong, he’s just walking around.

372
00:18:36,940 --> 00:18:37,660
Yes.

373
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:39,470
-She’s helping him find his style.
-Yeah.

374
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:41,740
I've told you

375
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:43,810
clothes have no gender.

376
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:46,950
Just wear what makes you feel confident.

377
00:18:47,150 --> 00:18:48,110
Got it.

378
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:55,980
Do I look cute in this?

379
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:01,560
You do.

380
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,330
Right?

381
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:07,440
Yep. Super cute.

382
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:10,440
Hey.

383
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:12,390
No, wait.

384
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:14,110
I mean…

385
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:18,840
It’s cute, but too basic.

386
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,760
Don’t worry, I’ll style you myself.

387
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:22,960
Let me help you.

388
00:19:25,730 --> 00:19:26,570
It’s not bad, though.

389
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:30,090
Such a Tsundere.

390
00:19:30,090 --> 00:19:31,980
He can’t fool us BL fans.

391
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,030
What?

392
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:37,360
Hey, Jeng.

393
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:37,980
Huh?

394
00:19:38,670 --> 00:19:39,810
Have you seen Mai?

395
00:19:40,580 --> 00:19:41,980
I haven’t seen him in a while.

396
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,360
Where did he go?

397
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:48,110
Mai, my friend.

398
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:50,070
Did you fall asleep?

399
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,500
I’m done.

400
00:19:56,250 --> 00:19:57,820
Holy shit!

401
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,490
How do I look, Leader?

402
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:19,850
A little less handsome than me.

403
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:24,600
Just a little?

404
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,980
Hello, Miss Jarassi.

405
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:44,330
Are you shopping for the boys again?

406
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:47,400
What can I get for you today?

407
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:51,330
The new collection, right?

408
00:20:51,530 --> 00:20:52,410
Yes.

409
00:20:52,410 --> 00:20:54,360
Just get everything I pick out.

410
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:55,490
Yes, ma’am.

411
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:58,080
Grab whatever you want.

412
00:20:58,080 --> 00:20:58,620
Okay.

413
00:20:58,620 --> 00:21:00,300
Tell me if you need anything.

414
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,190
Okay.

415
00:21:01,190 --> 00:21:02,240
Thanks.

416
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:04,700
Wow.

417
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,470
This one’s nice.

418
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:11,750
That’s from our newest collection.

419
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:14,310
It’s a little pricey, though.

420
00:21:24,110 --> 00:21:25,980
Excuse me.

421
00:21:26,330 --> 00:21:27,780
I’m sorry,

422
00:21:27,780 --> 00:21:31,560
but I’ve already reserved that one.

423
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:33,270
Do you want it back?

424
00:21:33,730 --> 00:21:35,520
I’m afraid I can’t.

425
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:38,270
I’m buying it for my boys too.

426
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:41,980
Then bring me a new one.

427
00:21:43,110 --> 00:21:45,210
I’m sorry, ma’am.

428
00:21:45,490 --> 00:21:47,980
That’s the last one we have.

429
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:54,510
Sir, you have to give me that outfit

430
00:21:54,510 --> 00:21:57,140
because I picked it first.

431
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:59,450
I should get it, right?

432
00:22:00,340 --> 00:22:03,290
But you weren’t going to buy it.

433
00:22:04,870 --> 00:22:06,450
If I picked it up first,

434
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:10,580
isn’t it mine by common sense?

435
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:13,530
I took it off the rack,

436
00:22:13,530 --> 00:22:15,230
not your hands.

437
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:17,540
So it’s still fair.

438
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:19,290
Excuse me, I’ll take this one.

439
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:23,070
I picked it first. The staff saw it too.

440
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:26,980
First come, first served.

441
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:30,200
Excuse me.

442
00:22:31,060 --> 00:22:33,170
I’ll take this one,

443
00:22:33,170 --> 00:22:35,690
this one, and this one too.

444
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:37,390
Please tell Mr. Nut

445
00:22:37,390 --> 00:22:40,720
to send the bill to my agency.

446
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:43,480
I’m sure he knows

447
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:46,090
who you should keep as a customer.

448
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:50,540
Not on my watch, Jarassi.

449
00:22:50,540 --> 00:22:53,040
I’ve already bought this one.

450
00:22:53,040 --> 00:22:57,470
If you steal it from me, you’ll have a serious problem.

451
00:22:57,730 --> 00:23:01,320
I’ll make a hashtag to drag your agency.

452
00:23:01,540 --> 00:23:03,460
Just so you know,

453
00:23:03,460 --> 00:23:07,690
I’m buying everything I picked.

454
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,440
You acted all excited,

455
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:13,630
wanting to buy everything I wanted.

456
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:16,100
Why didn’t you buy it earlier then?

457
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:19,290
Is it too expensive, so you can’t afford it?

458
00:23:19,670 --> 00:23:20,280
Huh?

459
00:23:22,480 --> 00:23:24,810
Well, you said it was expensive.

460
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:27,070
Excuse me, please pack it up for me.

461
00:23:27,070 --> 00:23:28,600
Go wrap it.

462
00:23:28,860 --> 00:23:31,330
Here’s my card. Take it.

463
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:34,270
Just remember,

464
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:36,880
other people have good taste too.

465
00:23:36,880 --> 00:23:38,250
You’re not special.

466
00:23:39,770 --> 00:23:42,930
Then I’ll take this one and this one. All of them!

467
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:44,220
I’ll take ten of each!

468
00:23:44,220 --> 00:23:46,670
Send the bill to my agency!

469
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,400
She totally ate.

470
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:51,450
Crazy bitch.

471
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:54,560
Hold on.

472
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:58,900
Everyone’s filming. What should we do?

473
00:24:00,090 --> 00:24:02,290
It’s nothing. We’re just shooting a series.

474
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,480
That’s right.

475
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,980
Cut. That’s a wrap. Great job.

476
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,650
Alright.

477
00:24:07,980 --> 00:24:09,460
Let’s move to the next spot.

478
00:24:09,460 --> 00:24:11,720
It’s okay, guys. You can all head out.

479
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,090
I’ll handle this. Go on.

480
00:24:14,270 --> 00:24:16,700
Leave it to me.

481
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,300
See you.

482
00:24:25,980 --> 00:24:27,980
Excuse me, ma’am.

483
00:24:27,980 --> 00:24:28,720
Yes?

484
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,860
Your card was declined.

485
00:24:30,860 --> 00:24:31,610
What?

486
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:32,970
Your card was declined.

487
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,450
Do you have a 0% installment plan?

488
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,040
Let me check our promotions for you.

489
00:24:54,220 --> 00:24:55,020
Mai.

490
00:24:56,090 --> 00:24:57,520
Do you think anyone saw us?

491
00:24:58,490 --> 00:24:59,410
Maybe…

492
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:04,250
Maybe it’s too late. We’re all over TikTok now.

493
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:06,800
It has more views than our entire album!

494
00:25:09,260 --> 00:25:10,190
What do we do?

495
00:25:11,590 --> 00:25:12,500
We’re doomed.

496
00:25:14,210 --> 00:25:15,000
Are you afraid?

497
00:25:16,690 --> 00:25:17,410
Hmm.

498
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,280
I’m afraid…

499
00:25:21,370 --> 00:25:23,040
that I’m not a good leader.

500
00:25:24,470 --> 00:25:26,330
Our group’s already hanging by a thread.

501
00:25:27,980 --> 00:25:29,540
This is gonna make things worse.

502
00:25:31,340 --> 00:25:32,340
Who said that?

503
00:25:34,220 --> 00:25:35,340
Your group

504
00:25:35,980 --> 00:25:36,990
is the best.

505
00:25:43,340 --> 00:25:46,650
You brought people with the same dream together.

506
00:25:47,510 --> 00:25:49,780
I think that’s really admirable.

507
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:53,090
People like you?

508
00:25:56,850 --> 00:25:58,930
If you have skills, but have no dream,

509
00:25:59,430 --> 00:26:01,050
I think it’s like…

510
00:26:03,730 --> 00:26:04,420
Oh.

511
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:06,390
Like a car with no gas.

512
00:26:07,120 --> 00:26:10,290
It can be driven, but it can’t go anywhere

513
00:26:11,130 --> 00:26:13,090
until someone fills it up.

514
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:17,320
Thanks for filling my tank.

515
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:22,700
Silly.

516
00:26:23,590 --> 00:26:25,490
You should ride a horse carriage.

517
00:26:26,220 --> 00:26:27,400
No gas needed.

518
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:29,130
And no pollution.

519
00:26:29,620 --> 00:26:30,460
Let’s get going.

520
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:31,490
Wait up.

521
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,620
Wait for me.

522
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:47,270
Here.

523
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:48,880
There’s a photo booth.

524
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:53,260
Wanna take some pictures?

525
00:26:55,220 --> 00:26:55,980
Sure.

526
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:02,480
This frame’s cute.

527
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,660
Whoa, it looks like Gel Boys.

528
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:07,200
Hey, are you trying something on me?

529
00:27:09,140 --> 00:27:10,250
Why would I?

530
00:27:10,740 --> 00:27:11,890
I’m just taking pictures.

531
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:13,870
Who’s gonna do anything to you?

532
00:27:16,620 --> 00:27:17,730
How about this frame?

533
00:27:18,260 --> 00:27:20,980
Wait, I haven’t done my handsome pose yet.

534
00:27:21,690 --> 00:27:23,140
You’re already handsome anyway.

535
00:27:24,770 --> 00:27:25,730
Say that again?

536
00:27:26,750 --> 00:27:28,080
No,

537
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:29,760
I mean…

538
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:32,370
we were so stiff at the poster shoot.

539
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,940
I wonder if we'll get better today.

540
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:38,690
We will. There aren’t many people looking.

541
00:27:40,220 --> 00:27:42,480
It’s just the two of us here.

542
00:27:45,540 --> 00:27:47,830
Alright, I’m pressing it.

543
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,300
Okay.

544
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:49,980
Let's go.

545
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:51,130
Oh!

546
00:27:51,860 --> 00:27:53,250
It’s counting down.

547
00:27:53,250 --> 00:27:54,120
What pose do we do?

548
00:27:59,460 --> 00:28:00,620
Next shot.

549
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:08,610
Hurry, it’s coming.

550
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,470
I'm almost out of frame.

551
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:25,430
Aren't we a bit too close?

552
00:28:25,980 --> 00:28:26,760
Why?

553
00:28:27,250 --> 00:28:28,770
It’s better when we’re close.

554
00:28:29,340 --> 00:28:31,170
So I can show everyone you’re mine.

555
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:34,090
Yours?

556
00:28:34,820 --> 00:28:37,220
You didn’t even have the guts to tell our friends.

557
00:28:37,470 --> 00:28:39,360
Aw.

558
00:28:40,070 --> 00:28:41,850
Please wait a little more.

559
00:28:42,130 --> 00:28:43,330
I’m not ready yet.

560
00:28:43,620 --> 00:28:45,100
But I have only you.

561
00:28:46,230 --> 00:28:47,880
No one else.

562
00:28:49,330 --> 00:28:50,450
Hmph, if I find out…

563
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:51,450
Mhm.

564
00:28:52,070 --> 00:28:53,020
You won’t.

565
00:28:53,020 --> 00:28:53,880
Huh?

566
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,840
I’m kidding.

567
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:57,740
It’s really just you.

568
00:29:03,270 --> 00:29:04,100
This one?

569
00:29:05,100 --> 00:29:05,750
Come on.

570
00:29:06,630 --> 00:29:07,880
Is it edible?

571
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:10,970
Where should we go next?

572
00:29:10,970 --> 00:29:12,280
Where do you wanna go?

573
00:29:13,980 --> 00:29:14,740
Hey!

574
00:29:15,980 --> 00:29:18,100
What were you two doing in there?

575
00:29:19,030 --> 00:29:19,670
Uh…

576
00:29:19,850 --> 00:29:21,490
Don’t tell me you were flirting.

577
00:29:21,490 --> 00:29:23,300
It’s not like that.

578
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:24,430
Yo, this is huge.

579
00:29:24,430 --> 00:29:26,250
What kind of fake news is that?

580
00:29:26,710 --> 00:29:28,080
I... I just went in

581
00:29:29,550 --> 00:29:30,700
to take an ID photo.

582
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:32,730
In that booth?

583
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:34,620
Bai Liu just walked by,

584
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:38,270
so I asked him to fix my hair.

585
00:29:38,270 --> 00:29:39,020
Right?

586
00:29:39,020 --> 00:29:40,960
Yes, I fixed his hair and left.

587
00:29:41,500 --> 00:29:42,460
-Really?
-Yes.

588
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:43,590
In that booth?

589
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:44,420
Yep, that’s it.

590
00:29:44,420 --> 00:29:46,090
But that’s a fashion photo booth.

591
00:29:47,270 --> 00:29:48,720
It’s basically the same.

592
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:52,120
Where else can I take an ID photo?

593
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,470
This is the only option. Stop overthinking it.

594
00:29:54,650 --> 00:29:56,970
Maybe I should take some too.

595
00:29:57,650 --> 00:29:58,320
Oh.

596
00:29:58,550 --> 00:30:01,380
We’re going to a cafe next.

597
00:30:01,380 --> 00:30:03,030
Wanna come? My treat.

598
00:30:03,290 --> 00:30:04,180
-For real?
-Yeah.

599
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:06,890
Okay, I’m in.

600
00:30:06,890 --> 00:30:07,560
Hold on, Si.

601
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:09,630
Can you buy these glasses for me?

602
00:30:09,890 --> 00:30:11,140
Yeah, let’s go.

603
00:30:13,980 --> 00:30:15,110
Come on, buddy.

604
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:18,660
You don’t have to pay a thing.

605
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:19,640
Really?

606
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:20,820
It's on me.

607
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:37,830
I’m back.

608
00:30:38,190 --> 00:30:39,440
How is it, Jarassi?

609
00:30:39,810 --> 00:30:41,020
I’m telling you,

610
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:44,310
everything went exactly as planned.

611
00:30:45,000 --> 00:30:46,480
Did he get suspicious?

612
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:51,470
He didn’t suspect a thing.

613
00:30:51,470 --> 00:30:54,080
I'm sure he can’t catch us.

614
00:30:55,270 --> 00:30:56,920
Good job.

615
00:30:58,090 --> 00:30:59,790
By the way,

616
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:02,190
can I ask you for something?

617
00:31:02,940 --> 00:31:04,370
Sure. Go ahead.

618
00:31:04,940 --> 00:31:06,380
The name Jarassi…

619
00:31:06,380 --> 00:31:09,450
was from when I lived in Korat.

620
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:13,600
Now I work with high society.

621
00:31:13,600 --> 00:31:15,830
And we’re at Siam Center now,

622
00:31:15,830 --> 00:31:18,630
so I wanna be called Shining.

623
00:31:19,630 --> 00:31:21,330
Oh, I see.

624
00:31:21,620 --> 00:31:23,510
-Shining.
-Yes, Shining.

625
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:27,580
Hi, girls. I’m back.

626
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:29,810
I’m back, guys.

627
00:31:30,320 --> 00:31:31,520
How’s it going, Jarassi?

628
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,610
Jarassi who?

629
00:31:33,610 --> 00:31:35,560
My name’s Shining.

630
00:31:36,230 --> 00:31:36,960
What?

631
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,070
Shining.

632
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,250
-That’s your name?
-Yes.

633
00:31:39,550 --> 00:31:40,380
Of course.

634
00:31:41,250 --> 00:31:43,830
You look like a guy, so it fits.

635
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:45,030
Huh?

636
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:46,940
Did you just say I look like a man?

637
00:31:47,260 --> 00:31:50,990
Your mustache looks like seaweed,

638
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:53,280
and your body’s like a bulldog.

639
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:54,110
Hey.

640
00:31:54,660 --> 00:31:55,790
Watch your mouth.

641
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:57,590
Don’t forget where you came from.

642
00:31:57,590 --> 00:32:01,150
Our moms are still making fermented fish paste in the countryside.

643
00:32:01,150 --> 00:32:03,850
No makeover can change that.

644
00:32:04,360 --> 00:32:06,260
Ow! You dare insult me?

645
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:07,730
You’re no different.

646
00:32:07,730 --> 00:32:11,160
Trying to act all Western with that look.

647
00:32:15,110 --> 00:32:17,850
Both of you, please stop.

648
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:19,890
Have some water first.

649
00:32:20,470 --> 00:32:22,520
Calm down, or people are gonna start looking.

650
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,810
But just now,

651
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:26,760
Shining was about to slap me.

652
00:32:28,310 --> 00:32:30,710
Slap you?

653
00:32:30,710 --> 00:32:34,870
No way. That was just hand exercise.

654
00:32:35,070 --> 00:32:37,890
It’s body training

655
00:32:38,340 --> 00:32:39,370
just like in the movies.

656
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:43,160
Do you know Reya?

657
00:32:45,190 --> 00:32:47,980
From Dok Som drama series?

658
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,970
Yes, you copied it so perfectly.

659
00:32:50,970 --> 00:32:52,570
Why don’t the boys notice?

660
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:53,720
That drama was iconic.

661
00:32:54,660 --> 00:32:56,350
How would they?

662
00:32:56,350 --> 00:32:59,190
It’s quite old.

663
00:32:59,190 --> 00:33:01,330
Kids these days don’t watch it.

664
00:33:02,420 --> 00:33:05,050
But our acting just now was so good.

665
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:06,750
I’m still in character.

666
00:33:06,750 --> 00:33:08,810
We could be actors for real.

667
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:11,980
Good thing you’re undercover at their agency.

668
00:33:12,580 --> 00:33:15,010
If they run into trouble or need anything,

669
00:33:15,250 --> 00:33:18,320
we’ll know right away and help directly.

670
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:19,400
Perfect.

671
00:33:20,260 --> 00:33:21,190
Oh gosh!

672
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:25,030
The clip of us fighting is blowing up.

673
00:33:25,030 --> 00:33:25,680
Huh?

674
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,240
It’s trending!

675
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:27,980
Let me see.

676
00:33:28,590 --> 00:33:30,210
I’m freaking out, Shining!

677
00:33:30,210 --> 00:33:32,370
What should we do?

678
00:33:32,370 --> 00:33:34,210
Relax. I’ll handle it.

679
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,330
Calm down. Don’t panic.

680
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:39,980
We’re screwed, Shining.

681
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:53,490
I think you guys are too tense.

682
00:33:53,490 --> 00:33:56,210
It’s almost like you’re meditating.

683
00:33:58,310 --> 00:34:01,230
I think we’re pretty chill.

684
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:02,960
Yeah, yeah.

685
00:34:04,710 --> 00:34:07,270
Why don’t you lean back a little?

686
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:09,750
The chairs have backrests.

687
00:34:12,630 --> 00:34:14,310
Excuse me.

688
00:34:14,310 --> 00:34:14,870
Yeah?

689
00:34:14,870 --> 00:34:17,750
Can I go to the bathroom?

690
00:34:17,750 --> 00:34:21,260
I’m so nervous I’m gonna pee myself.

691
00:34:21,489 --> 00:34:22,260
Uh…

692
00:34:22,260 --> 00:34:24,380
But we’re starting in a few minutes.

693
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:26,630
You might not make it back in time.

694
00:34:26,630 --> 00:34:28,290
Just hold it for now.

695
00:34:28,290 --> 00:34:32,239
Wait, did Jackson Wang come on this show?

696
00:34:32,239 --> 00:34:34,070
Chiquita, Ahyeon and Asa.

697
00:34:34,070 --> 00:34:36,280
Mabelz, Pimma and Ingkho from PiXXiE too?

698
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:37,380
Where did they sit?

699
00:34:37,380 --> 00:34:38,400
Uh…

700
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:39,699
They were in your seats.

701
00:34:39,699 --> 00:34:41,219
Ah, Mabelz!

702
00:34:41,219 --> 00:34:43,489
Today, I’m Mabelz.

703
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:46,260
You guys must be super excited.

704
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:50,520
Alright,

705
00:34:50,940 --> 00:34:54,230
should we start the show now?

706
00:34:54,600 --> 00:34:55,340
Sure.

707
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:56,270
Shall we?

708
00:34:56,270 --> 00:34:59,270
Yeah, let’s go.

709
00:34:59,730 --> 00:35:00,670
Ready?

710
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:01,600
Ready.

711
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,500
Okay.

712
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:08,410
Today, we’re here with the new wolves of T-Pop,

713
00:35:08,410 --> 00:35:09,910
Ahh Wolf!

714
00:35:11,090 --> 00:35:14,920
Yay!

715
00:35:17,390 --> 00:35:18,060
So?

716
00:35:19,180 --> 00:35:21,240
Ha… ha!

717
00:35:21,630 --> 00:35:22,420
Huh?

718
00:35:23,180 --> 00:35:25,220
Hana, Dul, Set!

719
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:29,650
Hi everyone, we’re Ahh Wolf.

720
00:35:29,650 --> 00:35:31,190
Awooo!

721
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:34,470
You guys must be really excited.

722
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:35,810
So,

723
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:38,660
I want you guys to introduce yourselves one by one.

724
00:35:38,660 --> 00:35:40,590
Starting from the left.

725
00:35:41,210 --> 00:35:42,070
Me?

726
00:35:42,070 --> 00:35:42,620
Yes.

727
00:35:47,090 --> 00:35:47,880
Hi.

728
00:35:48,150 --> 00:35:51,190
I’m Cutter. I’m the rapper.

729
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,370
And most importantly,

730
00:35:53,370 --> 00:35:56,660
I'm the writer of this song.

731
00:35:56,950 --> 00:35:58,240
You wrote this song?

732
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:58,970
Yep.

733
00:35:59,750 --> 00:36:01,480
Where did you get the inspiration from?

734
00:36:01,830 --> 00:36:02,500
Well,

735
00:36:02,970 --> 00:36:05,910
a talented and cool guy like me

736
00:36:06,140 --> 00:36:10,430
got the idea while eating chicken bitter melon noodles.

737
00:36:10,950 --> 00:36:14,400
Because someone didn’t wanna eat bitter melon.

738
00:36:16,020 --> 00:36:17,730
I see,

739
00:36:17,730 --> 00:36:20,850
so you wanted them to love it, right?

740
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:22,910
Exactly.

741
00:36:22,910 --> 00:36:24,050
You got it.

742
00:36:25,900 --> 00:36:26,790
Alright.

743
00:36:27,090 --> 00:36:28,880
Next, please.

744
00:36:29,970 --> 00:36:33,380
Hi, I’m Fong, the main dancer of the group.

745
00:36:33,380 --> 00:36:35,090
Please support our song,

746
00:36:35,090 --> 00:36:38,080
Er… Um… “Do you eat bitter melon?”

747
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,230
Oh.

748
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:41,430
Okay. Haha.

749
00:36:41,430 --> 00:36:42,690
Next member, please.

750
00:36:42,690 --> 00:36:45,460
Hi, I’m Yu, the main vocalist.

751
00:36:45,460 --> 00:36:47,420
Maybe not that vocal yet.

752
00:36:47,420 --> 00:36:48,380
Please take care of me.

753
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:50,210
Alright.

754
00:36:50,210 --> 00:36:51,230
Next, please.

755
00:36:52,330 --> 00:36:55,560
Hi, I’m Mai. I’m the newest member.

756
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:58,540
I basically follow the leader’s lead.

757
00:36:59,230 --> 00:37:02,470
Oh, follow the leader. Got it.

758
00:37:02,810 --> 00:37:05,860
Hi, I’m Jeng, the group leader.

759
00:37:05,860 --> 00:37:07,670
Please support us.

760
00:37:07,670 --> 00:37:08,290
Alright.

761
00:37:09,190 --> 00:37:12,840
I want to know how your song is doing right now.

762
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:17,350
The song?

763
00:37:17,350 --> 00:37:18,100
Yes.

764
00:37:18,100 --> 00:37:19,890
It’s really blowing up.

765
00:37:21,220 --> 00:37:24,220
Soon, everyone’s gonna be requesting this song on shows.

766
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:26,090
Yeah.

767
00:37:26,090 --> 00:37:29,090
Do you want to see our signature move?

768
00:37:29,250 --> 00:37:31,310
Come on. One, two, three.

769
00:37:31,310 --> 00:37:32,410
Woof woof.

770
00:37:32,990 --> 00:37:33,980
Woof woof.

771
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:37,980
Woof woof.

772
00:37:37,980 --> 00:37:42,200
You guys have really good chemistry.

773
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:47,860
I’m sure this song’s gonna be playing everywhere.

774
00:37:47,860 --> 00:37:50,470
But you’re still a new T-Pop group.

775
00:37:50,470 --> 00:37:54,160
Are you worried about the tough competition?

776
00:37:57,970 --> 00:38:00,470
Actually, we're...

777
00:38:00,470 --> 00:38:01,440
Not at all.

778
00:38:01,910 --> 00:38:02,690
I’m not worried.

779
00:38:02,900 --> 00:38:07,350
Soon, we’ll be the hottest rookie T-Pop group for sure.

780
00:38:07,820 --> 00:38:09,600
I’m not worried.

781
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:13,330
But I heard you guys are trending right now.

782
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:15,490
See? I told you.

783
00:38:15,490 --> 00:38:16,670
Yeah, you’re trending.

784
00:38:16,670 --> 00:38:19,950
There’s no way our song won’t blow up.

785
00:38:20,300 --> 00:38:23,580
We’re gonna shake up the whole T-Pop industry!

786
00:38:23,580 --> 00:38:25,770
You’re really going viral.

787
00:38:25,770 --> 00:38:29,110
Here, the views have already passed 100,000.

788
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,790
As you can see in the clip,

789
00:38:36,230 --> 00:38:38,680
it was pretty chaotic that day.

790
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:43,200
I’ll let the involved party explain it.

791
00:38:48,510 --> 00:38:51,780
I’m sorry, everyone.

792
00:38:52,230 --> 00:38:56,390
I didn’t mean to bring trouble to the company.

793
00:38:58,140 --> 00:38:59,920
But my secret is…

794
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:04,260
I’m a spirit medium.

795
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:07,910
If you don’t believe me,

796
00:39:08,450 --> 00:39:10,460
I’ll call her out and show you.

797
00:39:12,170 --> 00:39:13,520
Ngor Ngae, come out.

798
00:39:15,110 --> 00:39:16,400
Ngor Ngae, come out now.

799
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,600
They won't be scared.

800
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:22,220
Ngor Ngae is here.

801
00:39:22,220 --> 00:39:23,380
Haha.

802
00:39:23,380 --> 00:39:25,360
That day wasn’t a big deal.

803
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:29,830
I just got a little too rough while playing.

804
00:39:29,830 --> 00:39:31,300
Right?

805
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:34,040
There’s nothing to worry about.

806
00:39:37,310 --> 00:39:38,420
What just happened?

807
00:39:40,220 --> 00:39:42,840
Like you can see,

808
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:45,890
that day was so chaotic,

809
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:50,230
but we already apologized to the other party.

810
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:54,790
I’ll take full responsibility.

811
00:39:54,790 --> 00:39:56,130
It’s our fault.

812
00:39:57,030 --> 00:39:58,810
Right, Ngor Ngae?

813
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,280
Yes.

814
00:40:01,770 --> 00:40:03,730
I’m so scared.

815
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:11,790
Fake!

816
00:40:12,330 --> 00:40:13,320
So fake!

817
00:40:13,810 --> 00:40:15,380
They’re clearly acting.

818
00:40:15,380 --> 00:40:18,370
But Bai Liu really called to apologize to you.

819
00:40:19,130 --> 00:40:20,670
It’s just a publicity stunt.

820
00:40:22,580 --> 00:40:24,570
He’s scared his agency will face a backlash.

821
00:40:25,210 --> 00:40:25,920
Boss.

822
00:40:26,570 --> 00:40:29,930
Are we really going to T-stage next week?

823
00:40:30,150 --> 00:40:31,100
Of course.

824
00:40:31,940 --> 00:40:33,840
We’re going to that show

825
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:36,570
And make history.

826
00:40:39,140 --> 00:40:40,150
Boss.

827
00:40:41,210 --> 00:40:42,970
We won’t go to the wrong studio, right?

828
00:40:47,460 --> 00:40:48,410
Hey, guys.

829
00:40:48,410 --> 00:40:49,730
We got something big.

830
00:40:49,730 --> 00:40:50,910
Follow me.

831
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:52,700
What is it?

832
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:53,480
Quick.

833
00:40:58,780 --> 00:41:00,920
(Chicken bitter melon noodles)

834
00:41:01,380 --> 00:41:02,220
Whoa.

835
00:41:02,870 --> 00:41:03,480
No way.

836
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,460
Our fans really sent a food truck.

837
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:06,740
Come eat, guys.

838
00:41:07,160 --> 00:41:09,690
We have chicken bitter melon noodles.

839
00:41:09,690 --> 00:41:10,790
It looks good

840
00:41:11,090 --> 00:41:12,240
and tastes good as well.

841
00:41:12,860 --> 00:41:15,800
I can’t believe so many people are supporting us.

842
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:19,400
I’ve never even gotten a bottle of water.

843
00:41:19,860 --> 00:41:21,010
This is my first time.

844
00:41:21,510 --> 00:41:22,320
Exactly.

845
00:41:22,770 --> 00:41:24,270
I think

846
00:41:24,270 --> 00:41:27,600
we should make some content to thank the fans.

847
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:30,320
Yu, let’s do it.

848
00:41:30,660 --> 00:41:31,850
So,

849
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,270
I’ll make you eat bitter melon,

850
00:41:34,570 --> 00:41:38,790
and you have to act like it tastes good.

851
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:39,690
Okay?

852
00:41:39,690 --> 00:41:41,450
Sure. I’ll eat it all.

853
00:41:41,450 --> 00:41:42,400
Oh.

854
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,420
Are you happy, Leader?

855
00:41:46,190 --> 00:41:47,300
Of course.

856
00:41:48,340 --> 00:41:50,170
Are you happy too?

857
00:41:51,740 --> 00:41:53,690
I’ve been happy since the first day I joined.

858
00:41:55,750 --> 00:41:56,550
I’m getting shy.

859
00:41:56,550 --> 00:41:58,600
Yeah, this kind of thing makes you fold.

860
00:41:58,940 --> 00:42:02,040
Actually, I’m the mother of BL actors.

861
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:04,040
I’ve taken care of actors from every agency.

862
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:06,040
Ever since Love Sick the series .

863
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,360
Wait, since then?

864
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,200
Yeah.

865
00:42:08,200 --> 00:42:10,380
And what are you getting shy about?

866
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:13,180
Don’t you have a pairing like them? Do you want one?

867
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:15,010
Who would be interested in me?

868
00:42:15,330 --> 00:42:18,340
Just watching from afar is enough.

869
00:42:18,340 --> 00:42:19,660
Secretly watching?

870
00:42:20,330 --> 00:42:22,290
Look, your man is here.

871
00:42:23,070 --> 00:42:24,280
Go serve him some food.

872
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,340
He’s been taking care of your group for a while.

873
00:42:26,340 --> 00:42:28,980
Maybe you should take care of him too.

874
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:30,870
Would that be okay?

875
00:42:31,220 --> 00:42:32,400
Don't be such a chicken!

876
00:42:32,860 --> 00:42:36,040
These days, being gay is totally okay.

877
00:42:36,220 --> 00:42:37,550
Let’s go. Don’t care.

878
00:42:37,770 --> 00:42:38,500
Go for it.

879
00:42:40,170 --> 00:42:41,320
Congratulations, guys.

880
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:44,600
This is our big first step.

881
00:42:45,420 --> 00:42:46,480
From now on,

882
00:42:46,820 --> 00:42:49,700
our agency might have more supporters.

883
00:42:51,100 --> 00:42:51,850
Sean.

884
00:42:52,140 --> 00:42:54,040
Clear out the space next to our company.

885
00:42:54,550 --> 00:42:58,330
We might get tons of food support trucks after this.

886
00:43:01,410 --> 00:43:02,920
Then, we can eat nonstop.

887
00:43:06,150 --> 00:43:07,120
Sure, Medyer.

888
00:43:07,490 --> 00:43:08,970
Tell me if anything happens.

889
00:43:09,690 --> 00:43:10,520
Okay.

890
00:43:11,930 --> 00:43:13,240
Are you sure about this?

891
00:43:14,110 --> 00:43:14,840
Of course.

892
00:43:15,390 --> 00:43:17,140
If they only have bitter melon,

893
00:43:17,140 --> 00:43:18,840
and two grandma fans,

894
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,840
they’ll lose motivation

895
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:25,430
because their agency survives on the support of their fans.

896
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:28,840
You’re so kind.

897
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:30,700
If Tian finds out,

898
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:33,510
you two will definitely make up.

899
00:43:34,400 --> 00:43:35,730
No way.

900
00:43:35,730 --> 00:43:37,310
He doesn’t care about me.

901
00:43:38,260 --> 00:43:39,930
But back in college,

902
00:43:40,260 --> 00:43:44,210
he did ask you to get back together.

903
00:43:45,730 --> 00:43:47,030
Well…

904
00:43:58,910 --> 00:44:00,500
Guess who I am.

905
00:44:01,870 --> 00:44:02,820
Who is it?

906
00:44:05,470 --> 00:44:06,150
It’s me.

907
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:08,320
Where have you been?

908
00:44:08,780 --> 00:44:10,000
We only got to talk on LINE.

909
00:44:10,480 --> 00:44:12,630
It was so hard to meet you in person.

910
00:44:13,150 --> 00:44:13,800
Aw.

911
00:44:14,780 --> 00:44:16,400
I’ve been busy with my thesis lately.

912
00:44:17,220 --> 00:44:19,810
And Mai is about to debut in Korea soon.

913
00:44:20,610 --> 00:44:21,540
Wait, really?

914
00:44:22,040 --> 00:44:23,240
Mai is debuting?

915
00:44:23,500 --> 00:44:24,860
Congratulations!

916
00:44:25,300 --> 00:44:27,300
He's very dedicated since he was young.

917
00:44:27,640 --> 00:44:29,510
I knew he’d make it big.

918
00:44:31,390 --> 00:44:33,410
Everyone in my family is so excited.

919
00:44:34,060 --> 00:44:37,730
They want him to be like Nichkhun and BamBam.

920
00:44:39,380 --> 00:44:41,340
I kinda want to start a music label too.

921
00:44:43,450 --> 00:44:45,200
I want to revolutionize T-Pop.

922
00:44:46,080 --> 00:44:47,900
We dance TWICE songs all the time,

923
00:44:48,330 --> 00:44:50,480
so I want Koreans to dance to Thai songs too.

924
00:44:51,080 --> 00:44:53,220
But I don’t know if I can do it.

925
00:44:53,640 --> 00:44:54,670
I know you can.

926
00:44:55,450 --> 00:44:57,820
You can do anything, Bai Liu.

927
00:45:00,380 --> 00:45:03,500
So why did you call me here today?

928
00:45:06,030 --> 00:45:06,870
You…

929
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:10,320
You really don’t know what day it is?

930
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:12,220
Well…

931
00:45:12,870 --> 00:45:13,640
It’s Friday.

932
00:45:14,110 --> 00:45:15,550
Whoa.

933
00:45:19,810 --> 00:45:21,740
You forget your own birthday?

934
00:45:23,050 --> 00:45:24,230
Today is your birthday.

935
00:45:24,420 --> 00:45:25,100
Oh my god.

936
00:45:26,140 --> 00:45:28,440
I studied so hard that I forgot my own birthday.

937
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,150
Ah.

938
00:45:30,460 --> 00:45:31,640
Thank you

939
00:45:32,110 --> 00:45:33,210
for remembering it.

940
00:45:34,790 --> 00:45:35,750
I…

941
00:45:36,870 --> 00:45:39,740
I’d never forget my first love’s birthday.

942
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:41,480
Wait, what?

943
00:45:47,730 --> 00:45:48,610
My first love.

944
00:45:49,730 --> 00:45:51,160
Huh? What did you say?

945
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:54,430
My first love.

946
00:45:54,720 --> 00:45:56,180
Huh? I can’t hear you.

947
00:45:56,180 --> 00:45:57,820
My first love!

948
00:45:59,970 --> 00:46:01,770
I heard you from the start.

949
00:46:02,690 --> 00:46:04,900
Now you can say it out loud?

950
00:46:05,530 --> 00:46:07,400
You weren't this brave in front of other people.

951
00:46:08,610 --> 00:46:09,460
Well…

952
00:46:10,470 --> 00:46:13,500
I was just…

953
00:46:13,730 --> 00:46:16,390
So where’s my birthday present?

954
00:46:16,670 --> 00:46:17,820
I don’t see anything.

955
00:46:20,420 --> 00:46:21,530
Close your eyes.

956
00:46:27,740 --> 00:46:29,280
Don’t open them yet.

957
00:46:30,750 --> 00:46:31,900
Hurry up.

958
00:46:31,900 --> 00:46:32,850
Just a second.

959
00:46:34,380 --> 00:46:35,510
Can I open them now?

960
00:46:35,510 --> 00:46:36,890
Not yet.

961
00:46:38,750 --> 00:46:40,400
Okay, open your eyes.

962
00:46:44,310 --> 00:46:46,650
Where’s the present? There's nothing.

963
00:46:46,650 --> 00:46:48,130
Why make me close my eyes then?

964
00:46:48,420 --> 00:46:49,240
It’s me.

965
00:46:51,380 --> 00:46:54,010
I’m the present.

966
00:46:54,860 --> 00:46:55,660
Boo.

967
00:46:55,660 --> 00:46:57,340
I thought it’d be something special.

968
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:04,950
Then…

969
00:47:05,710 --> 00:47:06,700
Bai Liu,

970
00:47:07,430 --> 00:47:09,070
is there something special you want?

971
00:47:14,920 --> 00:47:17,350
Where’s the present?

972
00:47:18,410 --> 00:47:19,470
It’s me.

973
00:47:19,990 --> 00:47:21,110
I’m the present.

974
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:40,670
The real present

975
00:47:41,870 --> 00:47:42,960
is in the back seat.

976
00:49:26,590 --> 00:49:27,440
Ah!

977
00:49:27,770 --> 00:49:30,130
Did you get all heated up in the car?

978
00:49:30,800 --> 00:49:32,400
It’s not that heated.

979
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:33,460
The AC is on.

980
00:49:34,630 --> 00:49:35,480
Speaking of which,

981
00:49:36,540 --> 00:49:38,250
I want to bond with Conan.

982
00:49:39,760 --> 00:49:41,480
Huh? Conan?

983
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:43,140
You want to bond with Conan?

984
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:44,210
Yeah.

985
00:49:44,900 --> 00:49:47,080
Because my ultimate dream

986
00:49:47,080 --> 00:49:51,020
is to bond with the great detective, Conan.

987
00:49:57,540 --> 00:50:00,920
I’m willing to become a corpse for him to examine,

988
00:50:01,230 --> 00:50:03,600
bit by bit,

989
00:50:03,600 --> 00:50:07,460
so we’ll be closer,

990
00:50:07,460 --> 00:50:09,930
and be happy together.

991
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,200
Hey, where did you go?

992
00:50:13,760 --> 00:50:15,340
How could you leave me talking to myself?

993
00:50:15,820 --> 00:50:17,020
But it's alright.

994
00:50:17,530 --> 00:50:20,460
I'm happy living with Conan in my dream.

995
00:50:28,290 --> 00:50:29,380
Who are we missing here?

996
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:31,480
Wait.

997
00:50:31,770 --> 00:50:32,690
Where is Cutter?

998
00:50:33,060 --> 00:50:34,530
Where is he off to?

999
00:50:34,910 --> 00:50:37,550
I heard he went to fulfill a vow.

1000
00:50:38,320 --> 00:50:40,250
Now’s not the time for that.

1001
00:50:41,210 --> 00:50:42,550
It’s fine.

1002
00:50:42,550 --> 00:50:44,490
Cutter’s always late anyway.

1003
00:50:45,290 --> 00:50:47,190
He’s late again and again.

1004
00:50:48,230 --> 00:50:49,800
Hey.

1005
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:50,930
Whoa.

1006
00:50:51,810 --> 00:50:52,760
Chill.

1007
00:50:54,170 --> 00:50:57,610
I’ve got good news.

1008
00:50:58,240 --> 00:51:00,090
Our clip has over 10,000 views!

1009
00:51:00,090 --> 00:51:01,460
-Seriously?
-Yes.

1010
00:51:01,460 --> 00:51:02,460
The dance practice video?

1011
00:51:02,460 --> 00:51:04,570
Nope. The one where Yu and I

1012
00:51:04,570 --> 00:51:06,630
ate bitter melon chicken and thank our fans.

1013
00:51:06,630 --> 00:51:08,470
-Do you know what it is?
-It's bitter melon.

1014
00:51:08,470 --> 00:51:10,150
Such a good chemistry!

1015
00:51:10,410 --> 00:51:11,580
So, wanna be my love?

1016
00:51:11,930 --> 00:51:12,800
Are you happy?

1017
00:51:13,860 --> 00:51:14,870
Yes, I am.

1018
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:17,900
We’re blowing up.

1019
00:51:18,480 --> 00:51:22,590
I told you we’d make it big.

1020
00:51:23,100 --> 00:51:24,180
All thanks to this.

1021
00:51:24,940 --> 00:51:27,430
Here. Take a look!

1022
00:51:29,560 --> 00:51:32,670
I prayed all night, kept the Five Precepts,

1023
00:51:32,670 --> 00:51:34,750
and went to pray at every famous shrine.

1024
00:51:34,750 --> 00:51:37,870
There’s no way we’ll fail.

1025
00:51:37,870 --> 00:51:38,840
Wait.

1026
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:40,920
We already made a bitter melon song .

1027
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:42,180
How about this theme next?

1028
00:51:42,180 --> 00:51:43,320
Good idea.

1029
00:51:43,620 --> 00:51:44,700
But…

1030
00:51:44,700 --> 00:51:46,970
Cutter can’t even keep the first precept.

1031
00:51:47,330 --> 00:51:49,010
You always steps on ants.

1032
00:51:49,010 --> 00:51:51,630
I didn’t mean to. They’re too tiny.

1033
00:51:51,630 --> 00:51:53,260
No, you did it on purpose.

1034
00:51:53,260 --> 00:51:55,080
Oh, stop it.

1035
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:56,310
Why are you arguing with me?

1036
00:51:56,940 --> 00:51:59,540
I got a new idea after that clip blew up.

1037
00:51:59,910 --> 00:52:03,540
We should increase our fanbase.

1038
00:52:04,750 --> 00:52:06,870
How so?

1039
00:52:07,120 --> 00:52:08,050
Like this.

1040
00:52:08,310 --> 00:52:10,180
Just like the clip Yu and I made.

1041
00:52:11,100 --> 00:52:13,470
The trial dating thing.

1042
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:16,790
I think it’ll be interesting.

1043
00:52:17,070 --> 00:52:19,410
The more viral we get, the more fans we’ll have.

1044
00:52:19,410 --> 00:52:22,710
And the easier it’ll be to promote our songs.

1045
00:52:23,920 --> 00:52:24,860
Yeah.

1046
00:52:25,130 --> 00:52:26,040
Good idea, right?

1047
00:52:26,040 --> 00:52:27,260
-Yes.
-I agree.

1048
00:52:27,710 --> 00:52:30,180
So it’ll be Cutter with Yu.

1049
00:52:30,530 --> 00:52:32,440
And Jeng with Mai.

1050
00:52:33,170 --> 00:52:34,280
Two good parings.

1051
00:52:35,330 --> 00:52:36,510
So cute.

1052
00:52:37,570 --> 00:52:38,810
Hold up.

1053
00:52:39,820 --> 00:52:40,680
Me and Yu.

1054
00:52:40,910 --> 00:52:42,350
Jeng and Mai.

1055
00:52:42,350 --> 00:52:43,090
Yep.

1056
00:52:43,360 --> 00:52:44,460
What about you?

1057
00:52:45,570 --> 00:52:46,530
Who’s your partner?

1058
00:52:47,820 --> 00:52:49,120
Forget about me.

1059
00:52:49,750 --> 00:52:52,760
I’ll just help hype up your ships.

1060
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:55,370
No, we can’t do that.

1061
00:52:55,370 --> 00:52:57,570
Everyone has a partner.

1062
00:52:57,570 --> 00:52:59,500
You deserve to have one too!

1063
00:53:00,180 --> 00:53:01,140
Alright.

1064
00:53:01,550 --> 00:53:02,920
I’ll find you one.

1065
00:53:03,520 --> 00:53:04,380
Deal?

1066
00:53:08,670 --> 00:53:09,470
Who?

1067
00:53:10,530 --> 00:53:12,000
I got it!

1068
00:53:14,560 --> 00:53:15,340
You.

1069
00:53:15,620 --> 00:53:17,710
You’re paired with P’Sean.

1070
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:19,910
Me?

1071
00:53:19,910 --> 00:53:21,490
Yes, you.

1072
00:53:21,490 --> 00:53:23,100
You’re gonna be with Fong.

1073
00:53:24,180 --> 00:53:25,930
Is that really a good idea?

1074
00:53:25,930 --> 00:53:27,330
It sure is.

1075
00:53:27,330 --> 00:53:30,560
No idol group has ever shipped a member

1076
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:33,050
with the agency’s bodyguard.

1077
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:35,030
You got a point.

1078
00:53:35,030 --> 00:53:36,370
Are you sure?

1079
00:53:36,370 --> 00:53:37,590
My idea is fire.

1080
00:53:38,080 --> 00:53:39,590
We’re definitely going viral!

1081
00:53:41,080 --> 00:53:42,180
Alright then.

1082
00:53:42,180 --> 00:53:43,890
Let’s do it, guys.

1083
00:53:44,220 --> 00:53:45,230
Get to work.

1084
00:53:45,230 --> 00:53:47,560
Yu, you’re coming with me.

1085
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:50,600
And you guys go make your content.

1086
00:53:51,740 --> 00:53:54,280
P’Sean, let’s go make content together.

1087
00:54:04,840 --> 00:54:05,590
So…

1088
00:54:06,740 --> 00:54:09,450
Where should we go?

1089
00:54:12,160 --> 00:54:14,070
What places are close to this subway line?

1090
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:18,450
Oh.

1091
00:54:19,350 --> 00:54:20,620
Have you ever been to Talad Noi?

1092
00:54:20,840 --> 00:54:21,570
Not yet.

1093
00:54:27,530 --> 00:54:28,430
I’ll take you there.
